This directory contains the implementation of a tool for generating
a makefile for an ML-Doc document.  Given a list of ML-Doc input files,
it generates rules for the Info files. the HTML files (including the
index), and the proof LaTeX files.  The list of input files is specified
in a text file, with one input file per line (use "#" for comments).

Usage:
	mk-mldoc-makefile [options] file

Options:

	-bin dir		specifies the bin directory (default is
				installation specific)
	-html dir		specifies the HTML_DIR variable (default HTML)
	-info dir		specifies the INFO_DIR variable (default Info)
	-proof dir		specifies the PROOF_DIR variable (default Proof)

